{
  "id": "L4",
  "title": "Asking for Simple Directions",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "In this lesson, you'll learn how to ask a stranger for directions. Politeness is key! We'll use the formal 'u' for 'you'."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L4_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Pardon",
        "meaning": "Excuse me"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L4_V01",
      "data": {
        "Spreken": "To speak"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L4_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Spreekt u Engels?",
        "meaning": "Do you speak English?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L4_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "spreekt",
        "phonetic": "[spreːkt]",
        "tip": "The 'ee' sound is long, like in the English word 'speak'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L4_V02",
      "data": {
        "Het station": "The train station"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L4_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Waar is...?",
        "meaning": "Where is...?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L4_P02",
      "data": {
        "word": "station",
        "phonetic": "[staːˈʃɔn]",
        "tip": "This sounds very similar to the English 'station', but with a 'sh' sound at the end: sta-shon."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L4_S01",
      "title": "Getting Someone's Attention",
      "setting": "You're in the city center and need to find the train station. You decide to ask a friendly-looking person for help.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Politely get the person's attention",
          "chatbot_message": ""
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask if they speak English",
          "chatbot_message": "Ja?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask where the train station is",
          "chatbot_message": "Ja, een beetje."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Great start! Now, let's learn the essential words for understanding the directions you receive."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L4_V03",
      "data": {
        "Links": "Left"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L4_V04",
      "data": {
        "Rechts": "Right"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L4_P03",
      "data": {
        "word": "rechts",
        "phonetic": "[rɛxts]",
        "tip": "The 'ch' sound is a soft, scratchy sound from the back of your throat. It's a typical Dutch sound."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L4_V05",
      "data": {
        "Ver": "Far"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L4_V06",
      "data": {
        "Niet": "Not"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L4_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Is het ver?",
        "meaning": "Is it far?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L4_V07",
      "data": {
        "De straat": "The street"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L4_S02",
      "title": "Understanding the Directions",
      "setting": "The person has understood your question and is now starting to give you directions.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Acknowledge the first direction",
          "chatbot_message": "Ah, het station. Dat is makkelijk. Het is hier naar links."
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask if it is far",
          "chatbot_message": "Oké."
        },
        {
          "title": "Confirm the name of the street",
          "chatbot_message": "Nee, het is niet ver. Het is in de Hoofdstraat."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "To make sure you understood, it's a good idea to repeat the directions back. Let's learn how."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L4_V08",
      "data": {
        "Rechtdoor": "Straight ahead"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L4_V09",
      "data": {
        "En dan": "And then"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L4_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Dus...",
        "meaning": "So..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L4_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Dank u wel",
        "meaning": "Thank you very much"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L4_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Graag gedaan",
        "meaning": "You're welcome"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L4_E08",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Fijne dag nog",
        "meaning": "Have a nice day"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L4_S03",
      "title": "Finishing the Conversation",
      "setting": "You think you know the way. Now, confirm the directions and end the conversation politely.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Repeat the directions to confirm",
          "chatbot_message": "Ja, de Hoofdstraat. Ga links, en dan rechtdoor."
        },
        {
          "title": "Thank the person for their help",
          "chatbot_message": "Ja, dat klopt."
        },
        {
          "title": "Wish them a nice day",
          "chatbot_message": "Graag gedaan."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}